eventScripts.script:
#Update Period End of current year to current start of day selection
	currentQualifiedValue = currentValue
	previousQualifiedValue = previousValue
	if initialChange:
		return
	if currentQualifiedValue is not None and previousQualifiedValue is not None:
		currentStartOfDay = currentQualifiedValue.value
		previousStartOfDay = previousQualifiedValue.value
		#If current start of day is not the same as previous start of day then update current year time period in flow
		if currentStartOfDay != previousStartOfDay:	
			#Get database name
			database = Standard.Model.Common.TagRead("[.]Connection['Database']")
			if database is None:
				return
			#Get Time Period Dataset
			timePeriodDocument = Standard.Model.Common.TagRead("[.]Year TimePeriodID")
			if timePeriodDocument is None:
				return
			#Get Current Time Period ID
			timePeriodID = timePeriodDocument["TimePeriodID"]
			#Get Current Period End in local time
			periodEndLocal = system.date.parse(timePeriodDocument["PeriodEnd"])
			#Update periodEndLocal with new start of day
			newPeriodEndLocal = system.date.setTime(periodEndLocal,currentStartOfDay,0,0)
			updatePeriodEnd = Standard.InterfaceModules.Flow.PublicAPI.V1.Configuration.UpdateCurrentYearStartOfDay(database,timePeriodID,newPeriodEndLocal)

nextPeriodStartQualifiedObject = currentValue
	previousPeriodStartQualifiedObject = previousValue
	if nextPeriodStartQualifiedObject is not None and (previousPeriodStartQualifiedObject is not None or initialChange):
		logger = system.util.getLogger('NextPeriodStart')
		isEqual = True
		nextPeriodStart = nextPeriodStartQualifiedObject.value
		logger.info('nextPeriodStart:' + str(nextPeriodStart))	
		if initialChange:
			isEqual = False
		else:
			previousPeriodStart = previousPeriodStartQualifiedObject.value
			isEqual = nextPeriodStart.equals(previousPeriodStart)	
			logger.info('isEqual:' + str(isEqual))	
		#Only Run Script if value has changed
		if isEqual:
			return
		now = system.date.now()
		daysBetween = system.date.daysBetween(now,nextPeriodStart)	
		#Creation Offest to make sure Ignition isnt running multiple queries for all the sites at the same time
		offsetQualifiedObject = system.tag.readBlocking(["[.]TimePeriodsToCreatedDayOffset"])[0]
		offsetQualifiedObjectQuality = offsetQualifiedObject.quality
		offset = 1
		if offsetQualifiedObjectQuality.isGood():
			offset = offsetQualifiedObject.value
		logger.info('offset:' + str(offset))	
		logger.info('daysBetween:' + str(daysBetween))	
		if daysBetween<=offset:			
			logger.info('StartPeriod:' + str(nextPeriodStart))
			createCommandPath = "[.]Create Command"
			system.tag.writeBlocking([createCommandPath],[True])

logger = system.util.getLogger("TimeperiodsToCreate Change Script")
	createCommandPath = "[.]Create Command"
	createCommand = system.tag.readBlocking([createCommandPath])[0].value
	if createCommand == True:
		createCommandPath = "[.]Create Command"
		system.tag.writeBlocking([createCommandPath],[False])
		
		#Call Create Script
		timePeriodsToCreatedPath = "[.]TimePeriodsToCreated"
		refreshPath = "[.]Refresh"
		databaseTagPath = "[.]Connection/Database"
		tagValues = system.tag.readBlocking([timePeriodsToCreatedPath,refreshPath,databaseTagPath])
		timePeriodsToCreated = tagValues[0].value
		refresh = tagValues[1].value
		database = tagValues[2].value
		
		finalPeriodEndYear = Standard.InterfaceModules.Flow.PublicAPI.V1.Configuration.CreateTimePeriods(TimePeriodsToCreated=timePeriodsToCreated)
		logger.info("finalPeriodEndYear: "  + str(finalPeriodEndYear))
		#Update Current Year to year of Final End period created and refresh current periods using the refresh tag
		system.tag.writeBlocking([refreshPath],[not refresh])
		if finalPeriodEndYear is not None:
			currentYearTagPath = "[.]Year"		
			system.tag.writeBlocking([currentYearTagPath],[finalPeriodEndYear])

currentValueQualifiedObject = currentValue	
	previousValueQualifiedObject = previousValue
	if currentValueQualifiedObject is not None and (previousValueQualifiedObject is not None or initialChange):
		currentValue = currentValueQualifiedObject.value
		createTimePeriods = False
		if initialChange and currentValue:
			createTimePeriods = True
		elif initialChange == False and currentValue:
			previousValue = previousValueQualifiedObject.value
			if currentValue != previousValue:
				createTimePeriods = True
		#Only Create Time Periods if previous value was None or False
		if createTimePeriods:
			createCommandPath = "[.]Create Command"
			#Write False to tag to reset Create Command 
			system.tag.writeBlocking([createCommandPath],[False])			
			#Call Create Script
			timePeriodsToCreatedPath = "[.]TimePeriodsToCreated"
			refreshPath = "[.]Refresh"
			tagValues = system.tag.readBlocking([timePeriodsToCreatedPath,refreshPath])
			timePeriodsToCreated = tagValues[0].value
			refresh = tagValues[1].value
			Standard.InterfaceModules.Flow.PublicAPI.V1.Configuration.CreateTimePeriods(TimePeriodsToCreated=timePeriodsToCreated)
			#Refresh the refresh tag to requery the current Flow Time Periods
			system.tag.writeBlocking([refreshPath],[not refresh])

eventScripts.script:
#This script works under the assumption everything is in sync
	logger = system.util.getLogger("Change of Year")
	#Update Period End of current year to current start of day selection
	currentQualifiedValue = currentValue
	previousQualifiedValue = previousValue
	addNewYear = False
	#If initial change then also need to add current year
	if initialChange:
		addNewYear = True
		logger.info("initial change")
	elif currentQualifiedValue is not None and previousQualifiedValue is not None:	
		currentYear = currentQualifiedValue.value
		previousYear = previousQualifiedValue.value	
		#If current start of day is not the same as previous start of day then update current year time period in flow
		if currentYear != previousYear and currentYear>previousYear:
			addNewYear = True
			logger.info("current year greater than previous year")
	elif currentQualifiedValue is not None:
		addNewYear = True
		logger.info("current year is not none")
	if addNewYear:
		#Get New Year
		currentYear = currentQualifiedValue.value
		logger.info("currentYear: " + str(currentYear))
		#Get Current Start of Day
		currentStartOfDay = Standard.Model.Common.TagRead("[.]StartOfDay")
		logger.info("currentStartOfDay: " + str(currentStartOfDay) + str(type(currentStartOfDay)))
		#Get database name
		database = Standard.Model.Common.TagRead("[.]Connection['Database']")
		logger.info("database: " + str(database) + str(type(database)))
		if database is None:
			return
		#Get Calendar Name
		calendarName = Standard.Model.Common.TagRead("[.]Calendar Name")
		logger.info("calendarName: " + str(calendarName) + str(type(calendarName)))
		if calendarName is None:
			return	
		#Get New Year Start Period	
		newYearPeriodStartLocal = system.date.getDate(currentYear,0,1)
		newYearPeriodStartLocal = system.date.setTime(newYearPeriodStartLocal,currentStartOfDay,0,0)
		#Get New Year End Period	
		newYearPeriodEndLocal = system.date.getDate(currentYear+1,0,1)
		newYearPeriodEndLocal = system.date.setTime(newYearPeriodEndLocal,currentStartOfDay,0,0)
		#Get Params required to create new yeary time period
		params = {}
		params["database"] = str(database)
		#Standard.InterfaceModules.Flow.Common.Logmessage(LoggerName='CreateTimePeriods',Message="database: " + str(period["database"]),DebugLevel=10)	
		params["IntervalType"] = "Yearly"
		params["PeriodStart"] = newYearPeriodStartLocal
		params["CalendarName"] = calendarName
		params["PeriodEnd"] = newYearPeriodEndLocal
		#Create new yearly time period in Flow
		result = system.db.runNamedQuery(path='Flow/CreateManualPeriod',parameters=params)

#This script works under the assumption everything is in sync
	logger = system.util.getLogger("Change of Year")
	#Update Period End of current year to current start of day selection
	currentQualifiedValue = currentValue
	previousQualifiedValue = previousValue
	addNewYear = False
	#If initial change then also need to add current year
	if initialChange:
		addNewYear = True
		logger.info("initial change")
	elif currentQualifiedValue is not None and previousQualifiedValue is not None:	
		currentYear = currentQualifiedValue.value
		previousYear = previousQualifiedValue.value	
		#If current start of day is not the same as previous start of day then update current year time period in flow
		if currentYear != previousYear and currentYear>previousYear:
			addNewYear = True
			logger.info("current year greater than previous year")
	elif currentQualifiedValue is not None:
		addNewYear = True
		logger.info("current year is not none")
	if addNewYear:
		#Get New Year
		currentYear = currentQualifiedValue.value
		logger.info("currentYear: " + str(currentYear))
		#Get Current Start of Day
		currentStartOfDay = Standard.Model.Common.TagRead("[.]StartOfDay")
		logger.info("currentStartOfDay: " + str(currentStartOfDay) + str(type(currentStartOfDay)))
		#Get database name
		database = Standard.Model.Common.TagRead("[.]Connection['Database']")
		logger.info("database: " + str(database) + str(type(database)))
		if database is None:
			return
		#Get Calendar Name
		calendarName = Standard.Model.Common.TagRead("[.]Calendar Name")
		logger.info("calendarName: " + str(calendarName) + str(type(calendarName)))
		if calendarName is None:
			return	
		#Get New Year Start Period	
		newYearPeriodStartLocal = system.date.getDate(currentYear,0,1)
		newYearPeriodStartLocal = system.date.setTime(newYearPeriodStartLocal,currentStartOfDay,0,0)
		#Get New Year End Period	
		newYearPeriodEndLocal = system.date.getDate(currentYear+1,0,1)
		newYearPeriodEndLocal = system.date.setTime(newYearPeriodEndLocal,currentStartOfDay,0,0)
		#Get Params required to create new yeary time period
		params = {}
		params["database"] = str(database)
		#Standard.InterfaceModules.Flow.Common.Logmessage(LoggerName='CreateTimePeriods',Message="database: " + str(period["database"]),DebugLevel=10)	
		params["IntervalType"] = "Yearly"
		params["PeriodStart"] = newYearPeriodStartLocal
		params["CalendarName"] = calendarName
		params["PeriodEnd"] = newYearPeriodEndLocal
		#Create new yearly time period in Flow
		result = system.db.runNamedQuery(path='Flow/CreateManualPeriod',parameters=params)
